This paper deals with the problem of fairness in machine learning models, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields of computer science. However, given the focus on developing theoretical guarantees and modeling approaches to transfer fairness across domains, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
